title: Spoilers for Avengers Endgame
body:
My mom and I had an argument after we left the theater about the endings between Cap and Iron Man. So mom obviously isn’t an all out fan, but Cap is her favorite and Iron Man is mine, so she’d clearly defend the ending we got (but obviously with me as a Tony Stark fan I wasn’t.)

Mom: “Captain America has been working so hard during the entire Marvel story and he’s been through so much trauma. That man deserves a break.”

Me: “Captain America didn’t get blown up, kidnapped and tortured by terrorists literally the first three minutes into his first movie. Captain America didn’t have a wife or 5 year-old child waiting for him when he got back. He wasn’t the one who has been betrayed in nearly every movie he’s portrayed in, and isn’t the one who openly admitted that he wanted a break away from being a hero.”

I don’t think I’ve ever heard her shut up so quickly 😂

blog.description:
We stan perfect, generous, big-hearted geniuses on this blog.

Group text usernames, if different from regular name: (for reference)

Tony - Iron Dad

Peter - Underoos

Pepper - Teapotts

Rhodey - Platypus

Bruce - Green Bean

T'Challa - Pink Panther

Natasha - Brown Recluse

Clint - Legolas

Steve - Cap

Scott - Thumbelina

body:
Avengers as John Mulaney Quotes

Steve: I have a girlfriend now, which is weird because I’m probably gay for Bucky based on the way I act and behave and have walked and talked for the past 100 years.

Rhodey: I want to write songs for people in their 30s called “Tonight’s no good how about Wednesday? Oh you’re in Dallas Wednesday? Let’s not see each other for eight months and it doesn’t matter at all.”

Peter: Nah sister, you’re not getting me to no secondary location. You want it? Go get it! Street smarts!

Tony: When I went to college, I looked like I was 11 and I lived like a goddamn ninja turtle. I didn’t drink water the entire time. I lived on cigarettes and alcohol and Adderall.

Carol: I would never say, not even as a joke, that my wife Maria is a bitch and I don’t like her. My wife is a bitch and I like her so much.

Scott: 13-year-olds are the meanest people in the world. They‘ll make fun of you but in an accurate way.

summary: In Avengers: Endgame, when the Avengers are talking about a basis for their time travel “rules”, Rhodey references the movie Hot...
body:
About that scene in Endgame

In Avengers: Endgame, when the Avengers are talking about a basis for their time travel “rules”, Rhodey references the movie Hot Tub Time Machine. Many have caught this reference and remember that Sebastian Stan himself was in it.

Now this brought up the huge question of how both Bucky and Seb were in the same universe and many have concluded that there is a Sebastian Stan in the MCU that looks exactly like Bucky. During a panel, Seb even talks about what he thought would happen if the two lookalikes ever met.

Avengers: Endgame Star Sebastian Stan Weighs in on Hot Tub Time Machine Paradox

However, I was watching The Martian the other day and realized something else. This movie also stars Sebastian Stan as astronaut Chris Beck and, near the end of the movie, there are many mentions of our very own Iron Man.

So does this mean that there is a universe that has a famous astronaut named Chris Beck, an actor named Sebastian Stan, and Bucky “The Winter Soldier” Barnes who all look exactly the same? And no one questions this??

summary: I had this whole post credit scene planned out for Endgame, where we would see all the new or yet to be seen in theatres...
body: I had this whole post credit scene planned out for Endgame, where we would see all the new or yet to be seen in theatres superheros receive and open a package waiting for them at home, like at the end of Homecoming when Peter finds a package on his bed from Tony, containing his suit. So all these superheros would open the package waiting for them and in there would be a homemade superhero suit made by Tony Stark. That way all the superheros ever shown in the MCU would’ve made an appearance, a cameo at least, and it would’ve shown how vast the MCU is and it would’ve been beautiful. So we would’ve seen Matt Murdock finding this in his office, Jessica Jones just throwing it in the bin because “I thought there’d be booze in there”, and I don’t know anything about the Agents of Shield or anyone else but we’d see them all have their new suits too. And we would’ve seen other people from all around the globe that we don’t know yet and maybe never will, but they would have had their homemade suits too because that’s what Tony’s ending was in my head. Hanging up his own suit to live peacefully with his family but “tracking” all the superheros out there and making them their own suits to make sure they fight safely. Shaping the new generations of Avengers.
